WEBVTT

00:00.969 --> 00:02.302
Tessa: <i>It's inevitable.</i>

00:02.337 --> 00:04.507
<i>Sometimes, your friends</i>
<i>are going to make decisions</i>

00:04.539 --> 00:06.062
that you just don't agree with.

00:06.102 --> 00:07.469
I think I'm gonna cut bangs.

00:08.284 --> 00:12.535
<i>And sometimes, your only job</i>
<i>is to be supportive.</i>

00:12.570 --> 00:14.971
I think I'm gonna dye my bangs pink.

00:15.006 --> 00:17.807
<i>But if you watch your friend</i>
<i>make a decision</i>

00:17.842 --> 00:19.275
<i>that can hurt them</i>
<i>without speaking up...</i>

00:19.310 --> 00:20.777
I'm so sick of these bangs.

00:20.811 --> 00:22.679
I think I'm just gonna burn them off.

00:22.713 --> 00:24.848
<i>...then what kind of friend are you?</i>

00:24.882 --> 00:26.716
- Lisa, no!
- Aah!

00:26.751 --> 00:28.518
[ Exhaling sharply ] - Oh, God.
- Ow.

00:28.552 --> 00:31.021
<i>And the latest bad decision...</i>

00:31.055 --> 00:32.989
So, this weekend's the big weekend.

00:33.024 --> 00:34.491
The big weekend for what?

00:34.525 --> 00:36.326
My parents are going out of town,

00:36.360 --> 00:38.528
so I'm gonna ask Malik
for his hand in marriage.

00:38.562 --> 00:39.696
Oh.

00:39.730 --> 00:41.598
It's gonna be the most perfect
proposal ever.

00:41.632 --> 00:44.000
I'm gonna sweep that boy off his feet.

00:44.536 --> 00:46.003
Oh.

00:46.037 --> 00:47.971
You said that already.

00:48.006 --> 00:49.273
Sorry.

00:49.307 --> 00:50.883
Lisa, come on.

00:50.922 --> 00:53.657
Aren't we a little young
to be thinking about marriage?

00:53.691 --> 00:55.325
Okay, first of all, we are not
thinking about marriage.

00:55.359 --> 00:56.860
I am. Me.

00:56.894 --> 00:58.662
And while I may be young in age,

00:58.696 --> 01:00.330
I have lived well beyond my 17 years.

01:00.364 --> 01:02.229
I am an old soul, Tessa.

01:02.276 --> 01:04.275
- I was born old.
- Right.

01:04.307 --> 01:07.580
Also, Malik is
your first real boyfriend.

01:07.614 --> 01:09.682
Correct. And he also happens
to be my soul mate.

01:09.716 --> 01:11.651
Look, I know that you have yet
to experience

01:11.685 --> 01:12.618
that kind of love...

01:12.653 --> 01:13.753
Here we go.

01:13.787 --> 01:15.121
...but just because you and Ryan
didn't last

01:15.155 --> 01:16.589
doesn't mean that we won't.

01:16.623 --> 01:18.724
That's... a fair shot.

01:18.759 --> 01:19.926
Yeah.

01:19.960 --> 01:21.694
But I still don't see what the rush is.

01:21.728 --> 01:22.995
True love is the rush, Tessa.

01:23.030 --> 01:25.131
True love is urgent and pressing

01:25.165 --> 01:27.200
and in need of our immediate attention.

01:27.234 --> 01:30.403
This proposal is going down
with or without you,

01:30.437 --> 01:33.105
so get on board or step to the left,

01:33.140 --> 01:35.526
because this train
is leaving the station.

01:35.573 --> 01:39.073
Sync and corrections by atrn97g
for www.addic7ed.com

01:39.103 --> 01:42.051
Alih Jey: ♪ Last night I had
a pleasant nightmare ♪

01:42.082 --> 01:46.582
Suburgatory 3x08 - Catch and Release
Original air date March 26, 2014

01:46.616 --> 01:48.261
♪ Da, da, da, da

01:48.583 --> 01:49.717
Dalia: Okay.

01:50.853 --> 01:52.575
Nora: Oh, hey, Monique.

01:52.610 --> 01:54.911
I need you to make more
of an effort with the drains.

01:54.945 --> 01:56.579
Uh, I will.

01:56.614 --> 01:58.348
You know, you always say that,

01:58.382 --> 02:00.516
but the hair in our pipes
tells a different story.

02:00.551 --> 02:01.517
I'm sorry.

02:01.552 --> 02:02.752
I don't want you to be sorry.

02:02.786 --> 02:04.887
I just want you
to be better at your job.

02:07.458 --> 02:08.791
Hand me my purse.

02:08.826 --> 02:11.127
"Please" and "thank you"?

02:11.161 --> 02:12.762
[ Dogs barking ]
What was that?

02:12.796 --> 02:14.797
- Nothing.
- Rough day?

02:14.832 --> 02:16.866
Not at all.
It was actually kind of slow.

02:16.900 --> 02:20.536
So, uh, what are you thinking
for dinner?

02:20.571 --> 02:23.039
[ Toy squeaking ]
Okay, Geoff,

02:23.073 --> 02:25.608
I need you to pick the squeakies
up off the floor

02:25.643 --> 02:27.644
and put them where they belong.

02:27.678 --> 02:29.078
I feel like you're a teenager

02:29.113 --> 02:31.247
that I constantly have to tell
to clean his room.

02:31.281 --> 02:33.816
Clean your room, Geoff. Clean your room.

02:35.105 --> 02:36.919
How about Indian?

02:36.954 --> 02:40.256
There's great shrimp korma
down the street.

02:42.679 --> 02:45.714
Do you think there's
such a thing as soul mates?

02:45.749 --> 02:48.970
I... know you have yet
to experience that kind of love.

02:49.002 --> 02:50.136
What the...?

02:50.170 --> 02:52.393
Why does everyone
keep saying that to me?

02:52.441 --> 02:53.441
But yeah.

02:53.476 --> 02:54.776
Yeah, I think soul mates exist.

02:54.816 --> 02:57.693
I just think it's extremely hard
to identify them.

02:57.735 --> 02:59.903
I just don't understand
how you can be sure

02:59.937 --> 03:02.405
that you've met... the one.

03:02.439 --> 03:03.840
You can't be sure.

03:03.874 --> 03:05.108
But you need to be sure,

03:05.142 --> 03:07.383
which is what makes the prospect
of marriage so daunting.

03:07.413 --> 03:08.880
Lisa doesn't think it's daunting.

03:08.915 --> 03:10.849
She knows she wants to marry Malik,

03:10.883 --> 03:12.417
and she thinks I'm being a bad friend

03:12.452 --> 03:13.452
for not being supportive.

03:13.486 --> 03:15.621
Well, being blindly supportive

03:15.655 --> 03:16.722
does not make you a good friend.

03:16.756 --> 03:17.956
Being honest does.

03:17.991 --> 03:21.126
But now that you've been honest,
you have to back off.

03:21.160 --> 03:23.462
It's Lisa's decision, not yours.

03:23.496 --> 03:25.430
You can't let it ruin your friendship.

03:26.761 --> 03:28.128
[ Panting, whines ]

03:28.162 --> 03:30.718
Uh... not today, buddy.

03:30.749 --> 03:32.316
We're gonna take a little break.

03:32.351 --> 03:34.018
[ Whines ]

03:34.053 --> 03:35.333
From what? Doggie day care?

03:35.365 --> 03:36.566
No, from Nora.

03:36.600 --> 03:40.872
Yesterday, she was seriously
bossy and borderline rude.

03:41.451 --> 03:43.285
Did you call her on it?

03:43.320 --> 03:46.022
No. That would have been rude.

03:46.056 --> 03:48.326
You have to be honest, George.

03:48.358 --> 03:49.592
You have to be honest,

03:49.626 --> 03:52.027
and you can't let it
ruin your friendship.

03:52.062 --> 03:53.862
A wise man told me that.

03:53.897 --> 03:56.265
Yeah, and a wise-ass repeated it.

04:02.153 --> 04:04.288
So, I know the train
is leaving the station,

04:04.322 --> 04:08.492
and I just want you to know
that I am on board.

04:10.284 --> 04:12.329
Then let me see your ticket.

04:12.921 --> 04:14.798
Wait.
[ Laughs ]

04:14.833 --> 04:16.567
Seriously?

04:16.601 --> 04:18.168
Seriously.

04:24.627 --> 04:27.144
This means so much to me.

04:27.178 --> 04:29.446
I'm gonna keep this.

04:30.417 --> 04:32.916
And I know marrying Malik
seems crazy to you.

04:32.951 --> 04:34.518
But to me, it's crazy not to.

04:34.961 --> 04:37.529
My parents married young.
Malik's parents married young.

04:37.561 --> 04:39.696
We were bred for long-term monogamy.

04:39.730 --> 04:41.231
It's in our DNA.

04:41.265 --> 04:43.417
Well, I think that's great.

04:43.447 --> 04:45.001
I think it's great
that you know what you want

04:45.036 --> 04:46.202
and you're going for it.

04:46.705 --> 04:48.506
I'm going for it.

04:48.533 --> 04:51.535
[ Chuckling ]
Yeah.

04:58.269 --> 04:59.949
Go for it!

04:59.984 --> 05:01.542
[ Doorbell rings ]

05:03.137 --> 05:04.759
- Hi.
- Hello.

05:04.798 --> 05:06.933
<i>I was happy for Lisa.</i>

05:07.194 --> 05:09.028
[ Door closes ]
<i>So why did I feel sad?</i>

05:15.131 --> 05:17.287
<i>As Lisa rushed towards the altar,</i>

05:17.334 --> 05:19.093
<i>George took the opposite approach.</i>

05:19.132 --> 05:21.590
<i>Before things got</i>
<i>any further along with Nora,</i>

05:21.630 --> 05:23.481
<i>he decided to do a background check.</i>

05:23.536 --> 05:25.844
Oh, hey. Nora's not in today.

05:26.184 --> 05:27.649
Yeah, no. I know.

05:27.688 --> 05:30.757
I... I just stopped by to pick up...

05:30.791 --> 05:32.826
this ball with the fake mustache
attached to it.

05:32.860 --> 05:34.994
That's a really popular item.

05:35.029 --> 05:37.430
Oh, hey, George.
You know, Nora's not in today.

05:37.464 --> 05:38.545
Yeah, no. I know.

05:38.577 --> 05:40.366
He just stopped in
for the mustache ball.

05:40.401 --> 05:41.534
Those are a riot.

05:41.569 --> 05:42.802
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]
Yeah.

05:42.837 --> 05:44.604
Uh... you know what?

05:44.638 --> 05:45.772
Since I have you both here,

05:45.806 --> 05:47.740
you mind if I ask you a question?

05:47.775 --> 05:49.209
Shoot.

05:49.976 --> 05:50.989
Okay.

05:51.046 --> 05:53.829
Uh, is Nora a bitch?

05:56.856 --> 05:59.344
That was blunter than I had intended.

05:59.395 --> 06:00.297
Here's the thing.

06:00.331 --> 06:02.332
I know I'm putting you in
a very uncomfortable position,

06:02.367 --> 06:03.801
and I apologize,

06:03.835 --> 06:06.437
but I can't tell you how many
times this has happened to me.

06:06.471 --> 06:08.872
I get involved with someone,
I think I know who they are,

06:08.907 --> 06:10.987
and then... bam... they turn out
to be somebody else.

06:11.269 --> 06:12.470
And yesterday...

06:12.504 --> 06:13.704
I have to get back.

06:13.738 --> 06:16.779
Yesterday, Monique,
I glimpsed something.

06:17.452 --> 06:20.923
And I want to know
if I saw what I think I saw.

06:20.958 --> 06:24.060
Is Nora a big old bitch? Or not?

06:24.736 --> 06:26.670
[ Sighs ]
Is she a bossy boots?

06:26.923 --> 06:29.401
You tell me, Geoff.
Don't lie to me, buddy.

06:35.655 --> 06:36.766
Yes.

06:36.800 --> 06:40.169
That will be $13.48, please.

06:41.187 --> 06:43.407
<i>While George proceeded with caution,</i>

06:43.454 --> 06:46.447
<i>I was mad at myself for not</i>
<i>throwing it to the wind.</i>

06:48.103 --> 06:50.861
<i>Watching Lisa carpe diem</i>
<i>put me to shame.</i>

06:50.994 --> 06:52.461
<i>She knew what she wanted,</i>

06:52.511 --> 06:54.346
<i>and she wasn't gonna let it get away.</i>

06:56.386 --> 07:00.070
<i>I certainly wasn't ready</i>
<i>to marry my ex-boyfriend Ryan.</i>

07:03.760 --> 07:04.994
<i>But that doesn't mean</i>

07:05.028 --> 07:07.296
<i>I should have let him get away</i>
<i>without a fight.</i>

07:07.612 --> 07:08.712
[ Zipper closes ]

07:09.104 --> 07:10.923
<i>I had to go see him.</i>

07:11.501 --> 07:14.204
<i>But since I didn't have a credit card...</i>

07:20.052 --> 07:22.320
Is this gonna be enough?

07:23.345 --> 07:25.259
Could you please not put that
on my chair?

07:25.291 --> 07:26.425
Money is filthy,

07:26.459 --> 07:28.727
and I seriously can't believe
you still use it.

07:28.762 --> 07:31.363
Okay. Uh, where do you
want me to put it?

07:31.397 --> 07:33.665
In the hamper.

07:33.700 --> 07:34.767
Okay.

07:34.801 --> 07:37.770
I'm showing three direct flights
to Orlando.

07:37.804 --> 07:38.937
Mm.

07:38.972 --> 07:40.105
You know, make that two.

07:40.140 --> 07:42.987
I don't like the equipment
Delta uses on that route.

07:43.034 --> 07:45.680
Looks like I can get you a bulkhead,

07:45.712 --> 07:47.930
which is good, 'cause you have one.

07:48.712 --> 07:51.334
Are you gonna need a rental car?

07:51.374 --> 07:52.975
Um...

07:53.009 --> 07:54.910
I don't exactly know
where I'm going yet.

07:54.944 --> 07:56.712
I still need to get Ryan's dorm info.

07:56.746 --> 07:58.313
Mid-size or luxury?

07:58.742 --> 08:02.651
I see you in a Yaris
or something comparable.

08:02.960 --> 08:04.486
You're 25, right?

08:04.521 --> 08:06.989
No. Not right.

08:07.023 --> 08:09.481
We... go to school together.

08:09.521 --> 08:10.654
I know.

08:10.689 --> 08:13.557
But you seem like you've been
left back a lot.

08:13.959 --> 08:15.259
Bag.

08:18.363 --> 08:20.164
Thanks a lot for coming through
for me, Dalia.

08:20.198 --> 08:21.665
I really owe you one.

08:21.700 --> 08:23.000
No probs.

08:23.034 --> 08:25.255
It was seriously my pleasure.

08:29.504 --> 08:31.305
Wait.

08:31.339 --> 08:33.441
Why is my return flight to Lebanon?

08:33.481 --> 08:37.083
Like I told you, my pleasure.

08:40.741 --> 08:42.375
Enjoy your trip.

08:42.416 --> 08:43.349
[ Doorbell rings ]

08:44.058 --> 08:45.522
Tessa! Come in.

08:45.553 --> 08:46.720
Hi, Mrs. Shay.

08:46.754 --> 08:48.522
I was wondering if you had
Ryan's dorm info.

08:48.556 --> 08:50.791
Oh, did you have something
you want to deliver to Ryan,

08:50.825 --> 08:52.303
because we can hand-deliver it.

08:52.335 --> 08:53.842
Big game tomorrow.

08:53.882 --> 08:55.921
Shay clan is gonna be there
to support him...

08:55.945 --> 08:57.813
in more ways than one.
[ Chuckles ]

08:57.847 --> 09:00.316
Ryan gets so pent-up before the games.

09:00.350 --> 09:02.451
- You remember.
- He needs release.

09:04.208 --> 09:06.224
They paid for my ticket.

09:06.259 --> 09:08.126
It'll be good for you two
lovebirds to see each other.

09:08.161 --> 09:09.427
Yeah.

09:10.076 --> 09:12.364
Anyways, Tessa, what was it
that you had for Ryan?

09:12.398 --> 09:13.904
Oh, right. Yeah.

09:13.936 --> 09:15.183
Um...

09:15.792 --> 09:18.073
it was just, uh...

09:18.905 --> 09:20.893
this bag of my old clothes.

09:20.947 --> 09:22.047
Oh.

09:23.862 --> 09:25.129
Well, I'm sure he'll love this.

09:25.163 --> 09:27.197
Fred: That is gonna have to be
your carry-on, dear,

09:27.228 --> 09:29.166
because mine is full of deer jerky

09:29.201 --> 09:31.669
and June's is nothing but boy shorts.

09:31.703 --> 09:32.870
[ Laughs ]

09:33.631 --> 09:34.912
Oh.

09:42.920 --> 09:45.155
This is some real healthy fare

09:45.189 --> 09:46.942
you got going here tonight, Tracy.

09:46.974 --> 09:48.875
I'm just trying to keep dad's
cholesterol in check, ma.

09:48.909 --> 09:50.009
You don't like it?

09:50.044 --> 09:51.477
No, I... I like it.

09:51.901 --> 09:53.847
A little fibrous is all.

09:53.881 --> 09:55.886
Like something you'd feed a horse.

09:55.925 --> 09:57.964
[ Chuckles ]
I like it, aunt Tracy.

09:58.011 --> 10:00.956
Thank you, Shira.
Would you care for some more?

10:00.996 --> 10:02.263
Oh, no.

10:02.298 --> 10:04.866
What's this over here?

10:05.481 --> 10:07.716
That's quinoa, dad.

10:09.928 --> 10:11.103
Tastes like dirt.

10:11.133 --> 10:13.835
Okay, let's change the subject,
shall we?

10:13.869 --> 10:15.637
Lisa, anything new?

10:16.420 --> 10:17.772
Funny you should ask.

10:17.807 --> 10:19.074
There actually is something

10:19.108 --> 10:21.428
I'd like to share with the family.

10:21.777 --> 10:25.839
Last year, as you know,
Malik and I split up briefly.

10:25.886 --> 10:28.419
It was one of the darkest times
of my life.

10:28.453 --> 10:29.787
Prior to that, my karaoke song

10:29.821 --> 10:32.823
had always been "I'm So Excited"
by The Pointer Sisters.

10:32.857 --> 10:34.525
Ooh, that's a good one.

10:34.559 --> 10:36.994
But during that time,
I felt like I was just

10:37.028 --> 10:39.463
going through the motions,
so my karaoke song

10:39.497 --> 10:42.559
became "Automatic"
by The Pointer Sisters.

10:42.606 --> 10:44.540
I like that one, too.

10:44.754 --> 10:46.411
But then we reconciled.

10:46.444 --> 10:47.544
[ The Pointer Sisters'
"Jump (For My Love)" plays ]

10:47.579 --> 10:50.147
And I've never been happier.

10:50.447 --> 10:55.124
So, tonight,
my karaoke song became "Jump,"

10:55.171 --> 10:57.272
by The Pointer Sisters.

10:57.306 --> 10:59.240
And I'd like to sing that for you now.

10:59.275 --> 11:01.042
Uh, whoa, what's going on?

11:01.077 --> 11:03.157
Sounds like she's gonna sing us
some Pointer Sisters.

11:03.167 --> 11:04.031
[ Chuckles ]

11:04.066 --> 11:05.600
All right.

11:07.583 --> 11:10.351
♪ Your eyes ♪

11:10.386 --> 11:12.854
♪ Tell me how you want me ♪

11:13.829 --> 11:16.858
♪ Can feel it in your heartbeat ♪

11:17.332 --> 11:20.195
♪ I know you like what you see ♪

11:20.229 --> 11:21.596
Okay, Lisa!

11:22.329 --> 11:24.365
♪ Hold me ♪

11:24.400 --> 11:27.969
♪ I'll give you all that you need ♪

11:28.555 --> 11:31.372
♪ Wrap your love around me ♪

11:31.735 --> 11:35.009
♪ You're so excited,
I can feel you getting hotter ♪

11:35.044 --> 11:36.111
Oh, okay...

11:36.145 --> 11:37.625
[ Laughs ]
♪ Oh, baby ♪

11:37.672 --> 11:41.118
♪ I'll take down, I'll take you down ♪

11:41.141 --> 11:42.575
That's a bad girl.

11:42.593 --> 11:45.025
♪ Where no one's ever gone before ♪

11:45.079 --> 11:47.095
♪ And if you want more ♪

11:47.134 --> 11:51.913
♪ if you want more, more, more ♪

11:51.976 --> 11:53.710
♪ Jump! ♪

11:53.744 --> 11:55.211
♪ For my love ♪

11:55.246 --> 11:56.246
♪ Jump in ♪

11:57.041 --> 11:59.088
♪ And feel my touch ♪

11:59.125 --> 12:02.227
♪ Jump! If you want to taste
my kisses in the night ♪

12:02.520 --> 12:06.189
♪ Then jump, jump for my love ♪

12:06.223 --> 12:07.323
♪ Jump! ♪

12:07.358 --> 12:09.626
♪ I know my heart can make you happy ♪

12:09.660 --> 12:10.760
♪ Jump in! ♪

12:10.795 --> 12:12.929
♪ You know these arms can fill you up ♪

12:13.758 --> 12:17.167
♪ Jump! If you want to taste
my kisses in the night ♪

12:17.201 --> 12:20.816
♪ Then jump, jump for my love ♪

12:20.952 --> 12:24.653
Malik... will you marry me?

12:24.943 --> 12:26.577
- What?
- What?

12:26.610 --> 12:28.327
Oh, hell, no.
[ Music stops ]

12:28.850 --> 12:31.736
But I want to spend
the rest of my life with him.

12:31.770 --> 12:33.771
- Well, that's too bad.
- Malik's going to Howard next year, Lisa.

12:33.806 --> 12:35.707
He applied early acceptance.

12:37.443 --> 12:38.676
You did?

12:39.813 --> 12:41.401
I... I was gonna tell you if I got in.

12:41.435 --> 12:42.717
I haven't heard anything yet.

12:42.757 --> 12:44.357
Ruth: But you will.

12:44.392 --> 12:46.259
We're not gonna let you
throw away your future

12:46.293 --> 12:47.827
to marry some country-ass white girl

12:47.862 --> 12:49.963
who wants to be a child bride.

12:49.997 --> 12:51.131
I'm not a child.

12:51.165 --> 12:52.799
Chester: Neither is Malik.

12:52.833 --> 12:54.567
Now, that's a grown man there,

12:54.602 --> 12:57.837
18 years old, so let's let him
speak for himself.

12:57.872 --> 13:01.841
Yes. Please. Speak for yourself, Malik.

13:02.794 --> 13:05.673
Do you want to marry me or not?

13:07.965 --> 13:10.649
[ Dog barks in distance ]

13:10.933 --> 13:13.460
Lisa, wait!

13:15.256 --> 13:18.177
You didn't give me a chance to explain.

13:20.339 --> 13:22.573
[ Crying ]

13:29.618 --> 13:31.126
Can you stop crying for long enough

13:31.164 --> 13:33.132
to tell me what happened?

13:33.432 --> 13:36.088
[ Crying ]
The train went off the rails.

13:39.535 --> 13:42.231
Oh, God, I'm so embarrassed.

13:43.372 --> 13:44.732
[ Sniffles ]

13:46.919 --> 13:49.303
I guess he doesn't feel the way I do.

13:50.286 --> 13:51.716
What exactly did he say?

13:51.751 --> 13:53.952
It's not what he said.
It's what he didn't say.

13:54.825 --> 13:57.413
He didn't say yes.

13:58.091 --> 14:00.116
I'm sorry, Lisa.

14:00.321 --> 14:01.407
Are you?

14:01.447 --> 14:03.494
Yes. Hey, I was on that train.

14:03.525 --> 14:05.593
I showed you my ticket.

14:05.627 --> 14:06.761
[ Sniffles ]

14:06.795 --> 14:08.730
<i>As bad as I felt for Lisa,</i>

14:08.762 --> 14:11.394
<i>I had to admit I also felt relieved...</i>

14:11.443 --> 14:14.093
<i>relieved that Lisa</i>
<i>wasn't marrying Malik,</i>

14:14.898 --> 14:18.182
<i>and relieved that I wouldn't</i>
<i>have to see Ryan and June</i>

14:18.217 --> 14:20.218
<i>dancing at her wedding.</i>

14:26.353 --> 14:29.418
Heard you stopped by my job
not looking for me.

14:29.455 --> 14:30.914
Oh. Yeah.

14:30.940 --> 14:33.241
Well... well, I was actually
just picking up...

14:34.692 --> 14:36.452
...one... one of those.

14:37.078 --> 14:38.652
Can I ask you a question?

14:39.105 --> 14:41.139
What's going on with you, George?

14:45.353 --> 14:47.954
Nothing. What's...
what's going on with you?

14:48.560 --> 14:49.562
[ Scoffs ]

14:49.597 --> 14:51.598
We've been hanging out for months now,

14:51.632 --> 14:53.867
and just when I finally feel
like it's getting somewhere...

14:53.901 --> 14:55.945
I catch you being a big old bitch.

14:57.086 --> 14:57.982
What?

14:58.016 --> 14:59.791
Super rude to your employees...

14:59.827 --> 15:03.263
no "please" or "thank yous",
a total bossy boots.

15:03.419 --> 15:04.553
"Bossy boots"?

15:04.587 --> 15:07.022
I'm done getting duped, sister.

15:07.056 --> 15:08.657
I... I've been done getting duped.

15:08.691 --> 15:10.292
[ Chuckling ]
Who's duping you?

15:10.326 --> 15:12.627
Am I pretending
like I'm someone I'm not?

15:12.662 --> 15:14.529
So, I'm a little bossy at work.
I'll cop to that.

15:14.564 --> 15:16.331
But I'm the boss.

15:16.366 --> 15:20.001
Look, there's a million reasons
not to be with someone.

15:20.036 --> 15:22.337
They grind their teeth,
or they hog the blankets.

15:22.372 --> 15:23.405
I... I certainly hope not,

15:23.439 --> 15:25.173
because those are both deal breakers.

15:26.722 --> 15:28.745
But when you're into someone,

15:28.785 --> 15:30.686
none of that other stuff matters.

15:31.178 --> 15:34.190
You know, even if they do have
a poorly trained dog

15:34.224 --> 15:38.027
and a hang-up on their ex
and a teenage daughter

15:38.061 --> 15:40.663
and more facial hair
than you'd typically like.

15:41.336 --> 15:42.638
When you fall for someone,

15:42.705 --> 15:44.306
none of that other stuff matters.

15:44.802 --> 15:47.076
<i>George knew</i>
<i>what Nora was saying was true,</i>

15:47.110 --> 15:50.245
<i>and he also knew, in that moment,</i>

15:50.280 --> 15:52.403
<i>that he hadn't fallen for her.</i>

15:52.912 --> 15:54.325
I should go.

15:56.005 --> 15:57.823
I should let you.

