[ Sighs ]

16:22.284 --> 16:25.120
Well, thanks again for including me.

16:25.637 --> 16:27.028
Mm-hmm.

16:27.060 --> 16:30.639
It was really great getting
a chance to see Ryan play.

16:30.686 --> 16:31.847
Okay.

16:31.881 --> 16:34.910
Listen, I, uh... I don't want
you to beat yourself up.

16:34.957 --> 16:36.143
I'm not.

16:36.175 --> 16:37.537
It wasn't your fault.

16:37.571 --> 16:38.973
I know.

16:39.028 --> 16:42.161
I was in the stands.
I'm not the one who fumbled.

16:42.592 --> 16:44.209
Oh, boy.
[ Chuckling ] Okay.

16:44.243 --> 16:45.912
It's okay. It's okay.

16:45.952 --> 16:47.485
It's just a little strange

16:47.517 --> 16:50.853
that Ryan has never fumbled
before in his life.

16:50.887 --> 16:52.625
I think we can all agree

16:52.657 --> 16:53.978
that the most logical explanation

16:53.991 --> 16:56.349
is that some unholy force was at work.

16:56.390 --> 16:58.028
It could have also been the rain.

16:58.076 --> 17:02.127
Absolutely. It's not like you
put a curse on our son.

17:02.174 --> 17:04.259
Please, take your curse off our son.

17:04.282 --> 17:06.367
Okay, you know, I'm just gonna head out.

17:06.407 --> 17:07.400
Bye-bye.

17:07.431 --> 17:08.765
Drive safely.

17:09.993 --> 17:12.836
You know, Ryan's roommate
never even left the room.

17:14.338 --> 17:16.901
So, we didn't get a chance to...

17:18.943 --> 17:20.622
[ Laughs ]

17:20.654 --> 17:24.089
Oh, my God. Why didn't you say so?

17:24.124 --> 17:25.758
- That's it.
- Explains it all!

17:25.791 --> 17:27.159
How about a nice, warm breakfast?

17:27.194 --> 17:28.903
Oh, Sheila scrambles a terrific egg.

17:28.938 --> 17:30.403
I do.
[ Chuckles ]

17:32.647 --> 17:35.867
<i>It had been a while</i>
<i>since Lisa had slept over.</i>

17:35.902 --> 17:38.370
<i>And even though it was more</i>
<i>of a suicide watch</i>

17:38.404 --> 17:39.705
<i>than a slumber party,</i>

17:39.739 --> 17:42.374
<i>I was still glad</i>
<i>I could be there for her.</i>

17:44.043 --> 17:45.668
